25constexpr uint32_t kTimestampTicksPerMs = 90;
26constexpr int kSendSideDelayWindowMs = 1000;
27constexpr int kBitrateStatisticsWindowMs = 1000;
28constexpr size_t kRtpSequenceNumberMapMaxEntries = 1 << 13;

30bool IsDisabled(absl::string_view name,
31 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials) {
32 FieldTrialBasedConfig default_trials;
33 auto& trials = field_trials ? *field_trials : default_trials;
34 return absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup(name), "Disabled");
35}

38DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::NonPacedPacketSender::NonPacedPacketSender(
39 DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress* sender)
40 : transport_sequence_number_(0), sender_(sender) {}
41DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::NonPacedPacketSender::~NonPacedPacketSender() =
42 default;
43
44void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::NonPacedPacketSender::EnqueuePackets(
45 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets) {
46 for (auto& packet : packets) {
47 if (!packet->SetExtension<TransportSequenceNumber>(
48 ++transport_sequence_number_)) {
49 --transport_sequence_number_;
50 }
51 packet->ReserveExtension<TransmissionOffset>();
52 packet->ReserveExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>();
53 sender_->SendPacket(packet.get(), PacedPacketInfo());
54 }
55}

57DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress(
58 const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
59 RtpPacketHistory* packet_history)
60 : ssrc_(config.local_media_ssrc),
61 rtx_ssrc_(config.rtx_send_ssrc),
62 flexfec_ssrc_(config.fec_generator ? config.fec_generator->FecSsrc()
63 : absl::nullopt),
64 populate_network2_timestamp_(config.populate_network2_timestamp),
65 send_side_bwe_with_overhead_(
66 !IsDisabled("WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead", config.field_trials)),
67 clock_(config.clock),
68 packet_history_(packet_history),
69 transport_(config.outgoing_transport),
70 event_log_(config.event_log),
71 is_audio_(config.audio),
72 need_rtp_packet_infos_(config.need_rtp_packet_infos),
73 transport_feedback_observer_(config.transport_feedback_callback),
74 send_side_delay_observer_(config.send_side_delay_observer),
75 send_packet_observer_(config.send_packet_observer),
76 rtp_stats_callback_(config.rtp_stats_callback),
77 bitrate_callback_(config.send_bitrate_observer),
78 media_has_been_sent_(false),
79 force_part_of_allocation_(false),
80 timestamp_offset_(0),
81 max_delay_it_(send_delays_.end()),
82 sum_delays_ms_(0),
83 total_packet_send_delay_ms_(0),
84 send_rates_(kNumMediaTypes,
85 {kBitrateStatisticsWindowMs, RateStatistics::kBpsScale}),
86 rtp_sequence_number_map_(need_rtp_packet_infos_
87 ? std::make_unique<RtpSequenceNumberMap>(
88 kRtpSequenceNumberMapMaxEntries)
89 : nullptr) {}

91void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::SendPacket(
92 RtpPacketToSend* packet,
93 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info) {
94 RTC_DCHECK(packet);
95
96 const uint32_t packet_ssrc = packet->Ssrc();
97 RTC_DCHECK(packet->packet_type().has_value());
98 RTC_DCHECK(HasCorrectSsrc(*packet));
99 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
100
101 if (is_audio_) {
102#if BWE_TEST_LOGGING_COMPILE_TIME_ENABLE
103 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(1, "AudioTotBitrate_kbps", now_ms,
104 GetSendRates().Sum().kbps(), packet_ssrc);
105 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(
106 1, "AudioNackBitrate_kbps", now_ms,
107 GetSendRates()[RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission].kbps(),
108 packet_ssrc);
109#endif
110 } else {
111#if BWE_TEST_LOGGING_COMPILE_TIME_ENABLE
112 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(1, "VideoTotBitrate_kbps", now_ms,
113 GetSendRates().Sum().kbps(), packet_ssrc);
114 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(
115 1, "VideoNackBitrate_kbps", now_ms,
116 GetSendRates()[RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission].kbps(),
117 packet_ssrc);
118#endif
119 }
120
121 PacketOptions options;
122 {
123 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
124 options.included_in_allocation = force_part_of_allocation_;
125
126 if (need_rtp_packet_infos_ &&
127 packet->packet_type() == RtpPacketToSend::Type::kVideo) {
128 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_sequence_number_map_);
129 // Last packet of a frame, add it to sequence number info map.
130 const uint32_t timestamp = packet->Timestamp() - timestamp_offset_;
131 bool is_first_packet_of_frame = packet->is_first_packet_of_frame();
132 bool is_last_packet_of_frame = packet->Marker();
133
134 rtp_sequence_number_map_->InsertPacket(
135 packet->SequenceNumber(),
136 RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info(timestamp, is_first_packet_of_frame,
137 is_last_packet_of_frame));
138 }
139 }
140
141 // Bug webrtc:7859. While FEC is invoked from rtp_sender_video, and not after
142 // the pacer, these modifications of the header below are happening after the
143 // FEC protection packets are calculated. This will corrupt recovered packets
144 // at the same place. It's not an issue for extensions, which are present in
145 // all the packets (their content just may be incorrect on recovered packets).
146 // In case of VideoTimingExtension, since it's present not in every packet,
147 // data after rtp header may be corrupted if these packets are protected by
148 // the FEC.
149 int64_t diff_ms = now_ms - packet->capture_time_ms();
150 if (packet->HasExtension<TransmissionOffset>()) {
151 packet->SetExtension<TransmissionOffset>(kTimestampTicksPerMs * diff_ms);
152 }
153 if (packet->HasExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>()) {
154 packet->SetExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>(
155 AbsoluteSendTime::MsTo24Bits(now_ms));
156 }
157
158 if (packet->HasExtension<VideoTimingExtension>()) {
159 if (populate_network2_timestamp_) {
160 packet->set_network2_time_ms(now_ms);
161 } else {
162 packet->set_pacer_exit_time_ms(now_ms);
163 }
164 }
165
166 const bool is_media = packet->packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kAudio ||
167 packet->packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo;
168
169 // Downstream code actually uses this flag to distinguish between media and
170 // everything else.
171 options.is_retransmit = !is_media;
172 if (auto packet_id = packet->GetExtension<TransportSequenceNumber>()) {
173 options.packet_id = *packet_id;
174 options.included_in_feedback = true;
175 options.included_in_allocation = true;
176 AddPacketToTransportFeedback(*packet_id, *packet, pacing_info);
177 }
178
179 options.additional_data = packet->additional_data();
180
181 if (packet->packet_type() != RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding &&
182 packet->packet_type() != RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission) {
183 UpdateDelayStatistics(packet->capture_time_ms(), now_ms, packet_ssrc);
184 UpdateOnSendPacket(options.packet_id, packet->capture_time_ms(),
185 packet_ssrc);
186 }
187
188 const bool send_success = SendPacketToNetwork(*packet, options, pacing_info);
189
190 // Put packet in retransmission history or update pending status even if
191 // actual sending fails.
192 if (is_media && packet->allow_retransmission()) {
193 packet_history_->PutRtpPacket(std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*packet),
194 now_ms);
195 } else if (packet->retransmitted_sequence_number()) {
196 packet_history_->MarkPacketAsSent(*packet->retransmitted_sequence_number());
197 }
198
199 if (send_success) {
200 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
201 UpdateRtpStats(*packet);
202 media_has_been_sent_ = true;
203 }
204}

206void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::ProcessBitrateAndNotifyObservers() {
207 if (!bitrate_callback_)
208 return;
209
210 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
211 RtpSendRates send_rates = GetSendRatesLocked();
212 bitrate_callback_->Notify(
213 send_rates.Sum().bps(),
214 send_rates[RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission].bps(), ssrc_);
215}
216
217RtpSendRates DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::GetSendRates() const {
218 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
219 return GetSendRatesLocked();
220}
221
222RtpSendRates DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::GetSendRatesLocked() const {
223 const int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
224 RtpSendRates current_rates;
225 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumMediaTypes; ++i) {
226 RtpPacketMediaType type = static_cast<RtpPacketMediaType>(i);
227 current_rates[type] =
228 DataRate::BitsPerSec(send_rates_[i].Rate(now_ms).value_or(0));
229 }
230 return current_rates;
231}

262std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info>
263DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::GetSentRtpPacketInfos(
264 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers) const {
265 RTC_DCHECK(!sequence_numbers.empty());
266 if (!need_rtp_packet_infos_) {
267 return std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info>();
268 }
269
270 std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info> results;
271 results.reserve(sequence_numbers.size());
272
273 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
274 for (uint16_t sequence_number : sequence_numbers) {
275 const auto& info = rtp_sequence_number_map_->Get(sequence_number);
276 if (!info) {
277 // The empty vector will be returned. We can delay the clearing
278 // of the vector until after we exit the critical section.
279 return std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info>();
280 }
281 results.push_back(*info);
282 }
283
284 return results;
285}
286
287bool DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::HasCorrectSsrc(
288 const RtpPacketToSend& packet) const {
289 switch (*packet.packet_type()) {
290 case RtpPacketMediaType::kAudio:
291 case RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo:
292 return packet.Ssrc() == ssrc_;
293 case RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission:
294 case RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding:
295 // Both padding and retransmission must be on either the media or the
296 // RTX stream.
297 return packet.Ssrc() == rtx_ssrc_ || packet.Ssrc() == ssrc_;
298 case RtpPacketMediaType::kForwardErrorCorrection:
299 // FlexFEC is on separate SSRC, ULPFEC uses media SSRC.
300 return packet.Ssrc() == ssrc_ || packet.Ssrc() == flexfec_ssrc_;
301 }
302 return false;
303}
304
305void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::AddPacketToTransportFeedback(
306 uint16_t packet_id,
307 const RtpPacketToSend& packet,
308 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info) {
309 if (transport_feedback_observer_) {
310 size_t packet_size = packet.payload_size() + packet.padding_size();
311 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_) {
312 packet_size = packet.size();
313 }
314
315 RtpPacketSendInfo packet_info;
316 packet_info.ssrc = ssrc_;
317 packet_info.transport_sequence_number = packet_id;
318 packet_info.rtp_sequence_number = packet.SequenceNumber();
319 packet_info.length = packet_size;
320 packet_info.pacing_info = pacing_info;
321 packet_info.packet_type = packet.packet_type();
322 transport_feedback_observer_->OnAddPacket(packet_info);
323 }
324}

326void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::UpdateDelayStatistics(int64_t capture_time_ms,
327 int64_t now_ms,
328 uint32_t ssrc) {
329 if (!send_side_delay_observer_ || capture_time_ms <= 0)
330 return;
331
332 int avg_delay_ms = 0;
333 int max_delay_ms = 0;
334 uint64_t total_packet_send_delay_ms = 0;
335 {
336 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
337 // Compute the max and average of the recent capture-to-send delays.
338 // The time complexity of the current approach depends on the distribution
339 // of the delay values. This could be done more efficiently.
340
341 // Remove elements older than kSendSideDelayWindowMs.
342 auto lower_bound =
343 send_delays_.lower_bound(now_ms - kSendSideDelayWindowMs);
344 for (auto it = send_delays_.begin(); it != lower_bound; ++it) {
345 if (max_delay_it_ == it) {
346 max_delay_it_ = send_delays_.end();
347 }
348 sum_delays_ms_ -= it->second;
349 }
350 send_delays_.erase(send_delays_.begin(), lower_bound);
351 if (max_delay_it_ == send_delays_.end()) {
352 // Removed the previous max. Need to recompute.
353 RecomputeMaxSendDelay();
354 }
355
356 // Add the new element.
357 RTC_DCHECK_GE(now_ms, 0);
358 RTC_DCHECK_LE(now_ms, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max() / 2);
359 RTC_DCHECK_GE(capture_time_ms, 0);
360 RTC_DCHECK_LE(capture_time_ms, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max() / 2);
361 int64_t diff_ms = now_ms - capture_time_ms;
362 RTC_DCHECK_GE(diff_ms, static_cast<int64_t>(0));
363 RTC_DCHECK_LE(diff_ms, std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
364 int new_send_delay = rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(now_ms - capture_time_ms);
365 SendDelayMap::iterator it;
366 bool inserted;
367 std::tie(it, inserted) =
368 send_delays_.insert(std::make_pair(now_ms, new_send_delay));
369 if (!inserted) {
370 // TODO(terelius): If we have multiple delay measurements during the same
371 // millisecond then we keep the most recent one. It is not clear that this
372 // is the right decision, but it preserves an earlier behavior.
373 int previous_send_delay = it->second;
374 sum_delays_ms_ -= previous_send_delay;
375 it->second = new_send_delay;
376 if (max_delay_it_ == it && new_send_delay < previous_send_delay) {
377 RecomputeMaxSendDelay();
378 }
379 }
380 if (max_delay_it_ == send_delays_.end() ||
381 it->second >= max_delay_it_->second) {
382 max_delay_it_ = it;
383 }
384 sum_delays_ms_ += new_send_delay;
385 total_packet_send_delay_ms_ += new_send_delay;
386 total_packet_send_delay_ms = total_packet_send_delay_ms_;
387
388 size_t num_delays = send_delays_.size();
389 RTC_DCHECK(max_delay_it_ != send_delays_.end());
390 max_delay_ms = rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(max_delay_it_->second);
391 int64_t avg_ms = (sum_delays_ms_ + num_delays / 2) / num_delays;
392 RTC_DCHECK_GE(avg_ms, static_cast<int64_t>(0));
393 RTC_DCHECK_LE(avg_ms,
394 static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int>::max()));
395 avg_delay_ms =
396 rtc::dchecked_cast<int>((sum_delays_ms_ + num_delays / 2) / num_delays);
397 }
398 send_side_delay_observer_->SendSideDelayUpdated(
399 avg_delay_ms, max_delay_ms, total_packet_send_delay_ms, ssrc);
400}
401
402void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::RecomputeMaxSendDelay() {
403 max_delay_it_ = send_delays_.begin();
404 for (auto it = send_delays_.begin(); it != send_delays_.end(); ++it) {
405 if (it->second >= max_delay_it_->second) {
406 max_delay_it_ = it;
407 }
408 }
409}
410
411void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::UpdateOnSendPacket(int packet_id,
412 int64_t capture_time_ms,
413 uint32_t ssrc) {
414 if (!send_packet_observer_ || capture_time_ms <= 0 || packet_id == -1) {
415 return;
416 }
417
418 send_packet_observer_->OnSendPacket(packet_id, capture_time_ms, ssrc);
419}
420
421bool DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::SendPacketToNetwork(
422 const RtpPacketToSend& packet,
423 const PacketOptions& options,
424 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info) {
425 int bytes_sent = -1;
426 if (transport_) {
427 bytes_sent = transport_->SendRtp(packet.data(), packet.size(), options)
428 ? static_cast<int>(packet.size())
429 : -1;
430 if (event_log_ && bytes_sent > 0) {
431 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRtpPacketOutgoing>(
432 packet, pacing_info.probe_cluster_id));
433 }
434 }
435
436 if (bytes_sent <= 0) {
437 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Transport failed to send packet.";
438 return false;
439 }
440 return true;
441}
442
443void DEPRECATED_RtpSenderEgress::UpdateRtpStats(const RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
444 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
445
446 StreamDataCounters* counters =
447 packet.Ssrc() == rtx_ssrc_ ? &rtx_rtp_stats_ : &rtp_stats_;
448
449 if (counters->first_packet_time_ms == -1) {
450 counters->first_packet_time_ms = now_ms;
451 }
452
453 if (packet.packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kForwardErrorCorrection) {
454 counters->fec.AddPacket(packet);
455 }
456
457 if (packet.packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission) {
458 counters->retransmitted.AddPacket(packet);
459 }
460 counters->transmitted.AddPacket(packet);
461
462 RTC_DCHECK(packet.packet_type().has_value());
463 send_rates_[static_cast<size_t>(*packet.packet_type())].Update(packet.size(),
464 now_ms);
465
466 if (rtp_stats_callback_) {
467 rtp_stats_callback_->DataCountersUpdated(*counters, packet.Ssrc());
468 }
469}
